{{wiktionary|Nemesis|nemesis}}
'''Nemesis''' may refer to:

* [[Nemesis (mythology)]], in Greek mythology, a spirit of divine retribution against those who succumb to hubris
* [[Archenemy]], the principal enemy of a character in a work of fiction
{{TOC right}}

==Literature==
* [[Nemesis (Nobel play)|''Nemesis'' (Nobel play)]], an 1896 play by Alfred Nobel
* [[Nemesis (Momen play)|''Nemesis'' (Momen play)]], a 1944 play by Nurul Momen
* [[Nemesis (Christie novel)|''Nemesis'' (Christie novel)]], a 1971 detective novel by Agatha Christie
* [[Nemesis (Asimov novel)|''Nemesis'' (Asimov novel)]], a 1989 science fiction novel by Isaac Asimov
* ''Nemesis'', a 1989 fantasy novel in the ''Indigo'' series by [[Louise Cooper]]
* ''Nemesis'', a 1998 science fiction thriller by [[Bill Napier]]
* [[Nemesis (Nesb<U+00F8> novel)|''Nemesis'' (Nesb<U+00F8> novel)]], a 2002 crime novel in the Harry Hole series
* [[Nemesis (Angel novel)|''Nemesis'' (''Angel'' novel)]], a 2004 novel based on the ''Angel'' series
* ''Nemesis'', a 2004 fantasy series by [[Wolfgang Hohlbein]]
* [[Nemesis (Roth novel)|''Nemesis'' (Roth novel)]], a 2010 dramatic novel by Philip Roth
* [[Nemesis (Davis novel)|''Nemesis'' (Davis novel)]], a 2010 historical crime novel by Lindsey Davis
* "[[Exile of the Eons]]", a 1950 Arthur C. Clarke science fiction short story, later called "Nemesis"
* ''Nemesis'', by James Swallow, Book 13 in the [[Horus Heresy (novels)#book13|''Horus Heresy'' book series]]
* "Nemesis'", a poem by H. P. Lovecraft in ''[[Collected Poems (H. P. Lovecraft)|Collected Poems]]''
* [[Nemesis (comics)]], the name of several comics characters
* ''Nemesis'', a 1989 horror novel by [[Shaun Hutson]]

==Film and television==
* [[Nemesis (1992 film)|''Nemesis'' (1992 film)]], a 1992 science fiction film
