==Ships==
* [[HMS Nemesis|HMS ''Nemesis'']], the name of several Royal Navy ships
* [[USS Nemesis (1869)|USS ''Nemesis'' (1869)]], a U.S. Navy ship
* [[Nemesis (1839)|''Nemesis'' (1839)]], a British warship of the East India Company, used in the First Opium War
* [[OPV Nemesis|OPV ''Nemesis'']], an offshore patrol vessel of the New South Wales Police Force

==Video games==
* Nemesis, an arch-enemy in [[Catacomb 3-D#Catacomb Fantasy Trilogy|Catacomb Fantasy Trilogy]]
* [[Nemesis (Resident Evil)|Nemesis (''Resident Evil'')]], a.k.a. the Pursuer, a fictional character in ''Resident Evil'' universe
* ''[[Resident Evil 3: Nemesis]]'', a 1999 home video game by Capcom, the third in the ''Resident Evil'' series
* ''[[Zork Nemesis]]: The Forbidden Lands'', a 1996 PC based adventure game, the 11th in the 1977 ''Zork'' series
* Nemesis, a monster in the 2008 home video game ''[[Dark Sector]]'' by Digital Extremes
* Nemesis, an elite German squadron in ''[[Secret Weapons Over Normandy]]''
* [[Gradius (video game)|''Gradius'' (video game)]], a 1985 arcade game known outside of Japan as ''Nemesis''
* [[Nemesis (Game Boy)|''Nemesis'' (Game Boy)]], a Game Boy game, part of the ''Gradius'' series

